who's a tailor.

920
01:37:32,032 --> 01:37:34,032
He'll give you a job.

921
01:37:35,436 --> 01:37:37,676
And I've found you
somewhere to live.

922
01:37:37,681 --> 01:37:38,834
It's a nice place.

923
01:37:38,839 --> 01:37:40,839
Quite small, but it's nice.

924
01:37:42,009 --> 01:37:44,443
- You'll like it.
- Thank you.

925
01:37:46,280 --> 01:37:48,685
There are various
social programs,

926
01:37:48,690 --> 01:37:51,308
cultural stuff I
can sign you up for.

927
01:37:51,385 --> 01:37:54,081
And the public
library is very close.

928
01:38:00,561 --> 01:38:02,561
You read a lot?

929
01:38:04,798 --> 01:38:07,426
I prefer being read to.

930
01:38:12,072 --> 01:38:14,072
That's over now, isn't it?

931
01:38:23,617 --> 01:38:25,710
Did you get married?

932
01:38:25,786 --> 01:38:28,914
I did. Yes, I did.

933
01:38:28,989 --> 01:38:31,048
We have a daughter.

934
01:38:31,125 --> 01:38:34,561
I'm not seeing as much of her
as I'd like.

935
01:38:34,628 --> 01:38:37,153
I'd like to see
a great deal more of her.

936
01:38:39,400 --> 01:38:41,493
The marriage didn't last.

937
01:38:56,917 --> 01:38:59,385
Have you spent time
thinking about the past?

938
01:38:59,453 --> 01:39:03,253
- You mean with you?
- No.

939
01:39:03,323 --> 01:39:07,054
No, I didn't mean with me.

940
01:39:16,537 --> 01:39:17,868
Before the trial,

941
01:39:17,873 --> 01:39:20,303
I never thought
about the past.

942
01:39:20,374 --> 01:39:22,535
I never had to.

943
01:39:22,609 --> 01:39:24,873
Now?

944
01:39:26,146 --> 01:39:28,146
What do you feel now?

945
01:39:29,316 --> 01:39:31,648
It doesn't matter what I feel.

946
01:39:32,653 --> 01:39:34,780
It doesn't matter
what I think.

947
01:39:36,890 --> 01:39:38,890
The dead are still dead.

948
01:39:46,200 --> 01:39:48,200
I wasn't sure what
you'd learned.

949
01:39:48,202 --> 01:39:52,070
Well, I have learned, kid.

950
01:39:52,139 --> 01:39:54,539
I've learned to read.

951
01:40:08,422 --> 01:40:10,422
I'll pick you up
next week, OK?

952
01:40:19,433 --> 01:40:21,433
That sounds a good plan.

953
01:40:24,037 --> 01:40:27,700
We can do it quietly,
or we can make a fuss.

954
01:40:27,774 --> 01:40:29,774
Quietly.

955
01:40:31,645 --> 01:40:33,875
OK. Quietly.

956
01:40:36,617 --> 01:40:38,617
Quietly.

957
01:40:47,094 --> 01:40:51,121
- Take care, kid.
- You, too. See you next week.

958
01:43:03,830 --> 01:43:06,321
I've come to collect
Hanna Schmitz.

959
01:43:10,237 --> 01:43:13,502
Please. Please, take a seat.

960
01:43:38,799 --> 01:43:41,427
She didn't pack.

961
01:43:41,501 --> 01:43:43,799
She never intended to leave.

962
01:43:49,543 --> 01:43:53,001
'The talk was that
a new face...

963
01:43:53,080 --> 01:43:56,675
had appeared on the promenade,

964
01:43:56,750 --> 01:43:59,446
a lady with a little dog.'

965
01:44:06,493 --> 01:44:08,493
She left me a message.

966
01:44:10,097 --> 01:44:12,097
A sort of will.

967
01:44:14,067 --> 01:44:17,002
I'll read the bit
that concerns you.

968
01:44:24,778 --> 01:44:27,770
'There is money in
the old tea tin.

969
01:44:27,848 --> 01:44:30,612
Give it to Michael Berg.

970
01:44:30,684 --> 01:44:32,181
He should send it,

971
01:44:32,186 --> 01:44:35,348
alongside the 7,000
Marks in the bank,

972
01:44:35,422 --> 01:44:39,222
to the daughter who
survived the fire.

973
01:44:39,292 --> 01:44:41,453
It's for her.

974
01:44:41,528 --> 01:44:44,554
She should decide
what to do with it.

975
01:44:48,068 --> 01:44:50,901
And tell Michael
I said hello.'

976
01:46:09,182 --> 01:46:11,548
- Ms. Mather?
- Yes.

977
01:46:12,252 --> 01:46:14,379
- You're Michael Berg.
- Yes.

978
01:46:14,454 --> 01:46:16,454
I was expecting you.

979
01:46:17,724 --> 01:46:21,421
- Please.
- Thank you.

980
01:46:21,494 --> 01:46:23,853
So you must tell
me, exactly what...

981
01:46:23,858 --> 01:46:25,954
brings you to the
United States?

982
01:46:26,032 --> 01:46:27,182
I was here already.

983
01:46:27,187 --> 01:46:29,187
I was at a conference
in Boston.

984
01:46:29,202 --> 01:46:30,565
- You're a lawyer?
- Yes.

985
01:46:30,570 --> 01:46:32,810
I was intrigued
by your letter,

986
01:46:32,815 --> 01:46:35,633
but I can't say I
wholly understood it.

987
01:46:35,709 --> 01:46:39,736
- You attended the trial?
- Yes. Almost 20 years ago.

988
01:46:39,813 --> 01:46:42,729
I was a law student.
I remember you.

989
01:46:42,734 --> 01:46:45,649
I remember your
mother very clearly.

990
01:46:45,719 --> 01:46:49,587
My mother died in Israel
a good many years ago.

991
01:46:49,656 --> 01:46:53,092
I... I'm sorry.

992
01:46:53,159 --> 01:46:55,159
Go on, please.

993
01:46:56,930 --> 01:46:58,894
Perhaps you heard.

994
01:46:58,899 --> 01:47:03,700
Hanna Schmitz recently died.
She killed herself.

995
01:47:05,038 --> 01:47:07,038
She was a friend of yours?

996
01:47:08,008 --> 01:47:10,008
A kind of friend.

997
01:47:10,977 --> 01:47:13,002
It's as simple as this.

998
01:47:13,079 --> 01:47:14,871
Hanna was illiterate...

999
01:47:14,876 --> 01:47:17,448
for the greater
part of her life.

1000
01:47:17,517 --> 01:47:20,680
Is that an explanation
of her behavior?

1001
01:47:22,389 --> 01:47:24,653
- No.
- Or an excuse?

1002
01:47:24,724 --> 01:47:26,817
No. No.

1003
01:47:29,896 --> 01:47:33,627
She taught herself to read
when she was in prison.

1004
01:47:33,700 --> 01:47:36,362
I sent her tapes.

1005
01:47:38,972 --> 01:47:42,840
She had always liked...
being read to.

1006
01:47:49,716 --> 01:47:52,446
Why don't you start
by being honest with me?

1007
01:47:52,519 --> 01:47:55,579
At least start that way.

1008
01:47:55,655 --> 01:47:58,283
What was the nature
of your friendship?

1009
01:48:03,196 --> 01:48:06,029
When I was young,
I had an affair with Hanna.

1010
01:48:11,972 --> 01:48:13,935
I'm not sure I can
help you, Mr. Berg.

1011
01:48:13,940 --> 01:48:16,101
And...

1012
01:48:16,176 --> 01:48:18,337
...even if I could,
I'm not willing to.

1013
01:48:18,411 --> 01:48:21,039
I was almost 16
when I took up with her.

1014
01:48:21,114 --> 01:48:23,340
The affair only
lasted a summer.

1015
01:48:23,345 --> 01:48:25,345
But...

1016
01:48:25,919 --> 01:48:28,046
But what?

1017
01:48:33,893 --> 01:48:35,893
I see.

1018
01:48:37,831 --> 01:48:40,280
And did Hanna Schmitz
acknowledge...

1019
01:48:40,285 --> 01:48:42,598
the effect she'd
had on your life?

1020
01:48:44,337 --> 01:48:47,670
She'd done much worse
to other people.

1021
01:48:52,645 --> 01:48:54,645
I've never told anyone.

1022
01:48:58,685 --> 01:49:01,984
People ask all the time
what I learned in the camps.

1023
01:49:02,055 --> 01:49:04,785
But the camps weren't therapy.

1024
01:49:06,893 --> 01:49:08,618
What do you think
these places were,

1025
01:49:08,623 --> 01:49:10,623
universities?

1026
01:49:11,264 --> 01:49:13,858
We didn't go there to learn.

1027
01:49:13,933 --> 01:49:17,994
One becomes very clear
about these things.

1028
01:49:21,441 --> 01:49:24,137
What are you asking for?
Forgiveness for her?

1029
01:49:24,210 --> 01:49:26,974
Or do you just want
to feel better yourself?

1030
01:49:27,047 --> 01:49:30,881
My advice? Go to the theater
if you want catharsis. Please.

1031
01:49:30,950 --> 01:49:32,914
Go to literature.

1032
01:49:32,919 --> 01:49:36,116
Don't go to the camps.

1033
01:49:37,690 --> 01:49:40,124
Nothing comes
out of the camps.

1034
01:49:42,629 --> 01:49:44,688
Nothing.

1035
01:49:57,977 --> 01:49:59,977
What she wanted...

1036
01:50:00,747 --> 01:50:05,184
What she wanted was
to leave you her money.

1037
01:50:05,251 --> 01:50:08,084
- I have it with me.
- To do what?

1038
01:50:10,190 --> 01:50:12,190
As you think fit.

1039
01:50:22,936 --> 01:50:24,936
Here.

1040
01:50:33,079 --> 01:50:35,146
When I was a little girl,

1041
01:50:35,151 --> 01:50:37,880
I had a tea tin
for my treasures.

1042
01:50:37,951 --> 01:50:42,251
Not quite like this.
It had Cyrillic lettering.

1043
01:50:45,125 --> 01:50:48,390
I took it with me to the camp,
but it got stolen.

1044
01:50:48,461 --> 01:50:51,953
- What was in it?
- Sentimental things.

1045
01:50:52,031 --> 01:50:56,161
A piece of hair from our dog.
Some tickets to the operas...

1046
01:50:56,236 --> 01:50:57,924
my father had taken me to.

1047
01:50:57,929 --> 01:51:00,138
It wasn't stolen
for its contents.

1048
01:51:00,206 --> 01:51:04,108
It was the tin itself...

1049
01:51:04,177 --> 01:51:06,805
that was valuable,

1050
01:51:06,880 --> 01:51:08,880
what you could do with it.

1051
01:51:16,756 --> 01:51:19,691
There's nothing
I can do with this money.

1052
01:51:19,759 --> 01:51:21,676
I give it to anything
associated...

1053
01:51:21,681 --> 01:51:23,224
with extermination of Jews,

1054
01:51:23,229 --> 01:51:25,823
then to me it seems...

1055
01:51:25,899 --> 01:51:27,606
...like absolution, and that's...

1056
01:51:27,611 --> 01:51:29,330
something I'm
neither willing...

1057
01:51:29,335 --> 01:51:33,066
- nor in a position to grant.
- I was thinking maybe...

1058
01:51:33,139 --> 01:51:37,007
an organization to
encourage literacy.

1059
01:51:40,847 --> 01:51:43,372
Good. Good.

1060
01:51:43,449 --> 01:51:46,316
Do you know if there
is a Jewish organization?

1061
01:51:46,386 --> 01:51:48,216
I'd be surprised
if there isn't.

1062
01:51:48,221 --> 01:51:51,850
There's a Jewish organization
for everything.

1063
01:51:51,925 --> 01:51:55,019
Not that illiteracy
is a very Jewish problem.

1064
01:51:56,863 --> 01:52:00,128
Why don't you find out?
Send them the money.

1065
01:52:16,349 --> 01:52:18,349
Shall I do it in Hanna's name?

1066
01:52:20,286 --> 01:52:22,286
As you think fit.

1067
01:52:27,093 --> 01:52:29,093
I'll keep the tin.

1068
01:52:33,833 --> 01:52:35,833
Thank you.

1069
01:53:27,387 --> 01:53:29,333
- Where are we going?

1070
01:53:29,338 --> 01:53:32,120
I thought you liked surprises.

1071
01:53:32,191 --> 01:53:35,319
I do. I do like surprises.

1072
01:54:39,592 --> 01:54:42,390
Hanna Schmitz.

1073
01:54:46,733 --> 01:54:48,733
Who was she?

1074
01:54:50,370 --> 01:54:52,770
That's what I
wanted to tell you.

1075
01:54:54,941 --> 01:54:57,068
That's why we're here.

1076
01:55:05,251 --> 01:55:07,251
So tell me.

1077
01:55:18,564 --> 01:55:20,998
I was 15.

1078
01:55:23,569 --> 01:55:26,094
I was coming home from school.

1079
01:55:28,174 --> 01:55:30,174
I was feeling ill.

1080
01:55:31,310 --> 01:55:33,744
And a woman helped me.

